00:32:05.360 --> 00:32:14.059
I mean, there are questions on there about
regrets and guilt over taking chances, rather

00:32:14.059 --> 00:32:21.130
than regrets over not. There are questions
on faith versus reason. Any question that

00:32:21.130 --> 00:32:23.850
you'd like to particularly share your philosophy
on? We'll get the front of the line.

00:32:23.850 --> 00:32:28.240
&gt;&gt;Rainn Wilson: Well, but this is the great
thing, I think, is like no one cares. Look.

00:32:28.240 --> 00:32:33.039
I'm a weird-looking comic character actor
from a TV show. No one cares what I think.

00:32:33.039 --> 00:32:34.240
&gt;&gt;Jesse Nichols: With the microphone though.

00:32:34.240 --> 00:32:35.730
&gt;&gt;Rainn Wilson: With an awesome microphone.

00:32:35.730 --> 00:32:36.730
[laughter]

00:32:36.730 --> 00:32:42.409
And, but really. No one cares what I think.
And I think that's important. That's the last

00:32:42.409 --> 00:32:46.990
thing I wanna be doing is pontificating or
saying, "Here's what I believe." I think that's

00:32:46.990 --> 00:32:49.970
what celebrities do way too often.

00:32:49.970 --> 00:32:58.000
And it's just like, "Shut up, man." So this
is a place for--. This isn't what I believe.

00:32:58.000 --> 00:33:02.169
What I believe is that we're human beings
and we all have a lot of the same thoughts

00:33:02.169 --> 00:33:09.740
and feelings and emotions. And when we experience
death in our families, or illness, or trouble,

00:33:09.740 --> 00:33:15.559
or beauty, like, we share things. Our neurons
fire in the same ways and there's a collective

00:33:15.559 --> 00:33:17.210
transcendent consciousness to that.

00:33:17.210 --> 00:33:23.019
And let's explore that realm. It's a little
bit underexplored. That's what I believe and

00:33:23.019 --> 00:33:29.769
that's what Soul Pancake's about. So, my specific
beliefs about my faith, or regrets, or this

00:33:29.769 --> 00:33:34.700
