00:37:43.141 --> 00:37:44.141
&gt;&gt;Rainn Wilson: Yeah.

00:37:44.141 --> 00:37:45.141
&gt;&gt;Female Audience Member #1: So you said earlier
in your talk that we have all these areas

00:37:45.141 --> 00:37:46.141
of our life that are fragmented, family, work,
friends. Yet we hear in our professional life,

00:37:46.141 --> 00:37:47.141
that it's really important to separate, if
you wanna be most professional, separate work

00:37:47.141 --> 00:37:50.070
and your personal life.

00:37:50.070 --> 00:37:58.510
It sounds to me like what you're saying is
that the best way to live is to meld all of

00:37:58.510 --> 00:38:15.200
these things together. And if that's not the
case, could you clarify, or tell us, how you

00:38:15.200 --> 00:38:18.390
think we could remedy having all these fragmented
bits of our life, other than what you've talked

00:38:18.390 --> 00:38:19.390
about just coming together and talking about
kind of important questions?

00:38:19.390 --> 00:38:28.030
Or, are there other things we could do to
unify our existence, for lack of a better

00:38:28.030 --> 00:38:29.030
words?

00:38:29.030 --> 00:38:34.400
&gt;&gt;Rainn Wilson: Yeah. That's an excellent
question and very specific. I appreciate it.

00:38:34.400 --> 00:38:39.640
I think that what I'm talking about is not
necessarily melding them and bringing them

00:38:39.640 --> 00:38:47.960
all together, but viewing them all as a whole.

00:38:47.960 --> 00:38:54.260
I think that just earlier this morning, it
was interesting. We took my son over to park

00:38:54.260 --> 00:39:00.250
over here, Shoreline Park, to play around
on a playground and there was this dad there

00:39:00.250 --> 00:39:05.250
with a Bible. And he was reading the Bible
and he had two kids there. And I'm not meaning

00:39:05.250 --> 00:39:11.820
to mock on anyone who reads the Bible or Christians
at all, 'cause I really love the Bible and

00:39:11.820 --> 00:39:12.820
I respect it greatly.

00:39:12.820 --> 00:39:19.020
But he was reading the Bible and his kids
were running around and one kid had his shoes

00:39:19.020 --> 00:39:24.462
off and was running around in the dew grass
and his feet were all muddy and weird and

00:39:24.462 --> 00:39:27.410
he didn't even notice. And sometimes the kids
would come over and they'd wanna talk to him,

00:39:27.410 --> 00:39:31.710
but he would like shrug them off and he was
just reading his Bible.

00:39:31.710 --> 00:39:35.589
And it was like, "Wait a minute! Dad, you're
missing the spiritual moment. The spirituality

00:39:35.589 --> 00:39:43.740
is with your kids in the sunshine, experiencing
life and taking in each breath and seeing

00:39:43.740 --> 00:39:53.480
them grow and socialize." And if you're looking
for something, what would Jesus do? Jesus

00:39:53.480 --> 00:39:56.240
would play with the kids. You know what I
mean?

00:39:56.240 --> 00:40:00.420
So it's, in a way, that's what I'm talking
about. It's a fragmentation where things are

00:40:00.420 --> 00:40:06.160
viewed as very separate, but it's all one
expression of what it is to be human. When

00:40:06.160 --> 00:40:10.760
people talk about spirituality and religion,
they get a really bad rap in this day and

00:40:10.760 --> 00:40:15.460
age. And I think really what we've done is
just thrown the baby out with the bathwater.

00:40:15.460 --> 00:40:19.330
It's like, "Well, religions are stupid and
people kill each other in their name and it's

00:40:19.330 --> 00:40:23.750
a stupid superstition. So we throw it out.
And it doesn't exist." You know what I mean?

00:40:23.750 --> 00:40:29.810
It's like, well, wait a minute. There is something
to--. It's interesting that most Americans

00:40:29.810 --> 00:40:32.339
describe themselves as spiritual, but not
religious.

00:40:32.339 --> 00:40:38.810
But spirituality is very important to Americans.
So I'm talking about is that spirituality

00:40:38.810 --> 00:40:43.520
is your work, your occupation, and being of
service and providing the tools that Google

00:40:43.520 --> 00:40:47.200
provides for the world community. I mean,
it's free. You get to use a search engine

00:40:47.200 --> 00:40:51.690
and you have this great email and do all this
really cool stuff, including the Wave and

00:40:51.690 --> 00:40:53.040
Chrome that no one ever uses.

00:40:53.040 --> 00:40:56.570
[laughter]

00:40:56.570 --> 00:41:03.310
You get to, you do all this stuff for free
and it's a great service. And that your occupation

00:41:03.310 --> 00:41:08.160
is the same as worship. And your family and
being of service to them is the same as worship.

00:41:08.160 --> 00:41:11.839
And your friends and fostering friendships
and bringing people together is worship. And

00:41:11.839 --> 00:41:14.640
being in the park with your kids is worship.

00:41:14.640 --> 00:41:21.960
And it's all a human expression. So rather
than thinking of it in these compartments,

00:41:21.960 --> 00:41:27.730
"This is what I do for this, this, that, and
the other thing", that it's all one greater

00:41:27.730 --> 00:41:35.410
transcendent social human need. And you don't
even have to believe in God to think that.

00:41:35.410 --> 00:41:42.380
You know what I mean. I don't know if that
clarified it, but that's my thoughts.

00:41:42.380 --> 00:41:45.900
&gt;&gt;Female Audience Member #1: It does. Thanks.

00:41:45.900 --> 00:41:46.900
